VALUES ('D.K. Deewana', 'Kedarnath Bhattacharya (born 20 October 1957), professionally known as Kumar Sanu, is an Indian playback singer primarily known for his performances in Hindi film songs and in Bollywood. He has won five consecutive Filmfare Awards for Best Male Playback Singer from 1991 to 1995. He holds a Guinness World Record for recording the highest number of songs in a single day, with 28 songs recorded in total since 1993. In addition to Hindi, Kumar Sanu has also sung in a wide array of languages, such as Bengali (his mother tongue), Marathi, Nepali, Assamese, Bhojpuri, Gujarati, Manipuri, Telugu, Malayalam, Kannada, Tamil, Punjabi, Odia, Chhattisgarhi, Urdu, Pali, and English. His songs receive consistently high levels of engagement across India, particularly with compositions that are sad and romantic in nature. 
