VALUES ('Gautam Chatterjee', 'Gautam Chattopadhyay (Bengali: গৌতম চট্টোপাধ্যায়) was an Indian Bengali singer, songwriter, guitarist, and composer. In 1975, as a leader he founded the progressive rock band Moheener Ghoraguli with Tapas Das,  Abraham Mazumdar, Pradip Chatterjee,  Ranjon Ghoshal, Biswanath Bishu Chattopadhyay, Tapesh Bandopadhyay. He was also a theatre personality, filmmaker, and ethnographer.
