VALUES ('Laxmikant Kudalkar', 'Alka Yagnik (born 20 March 1966) is a Indian playback singer who worked predominantly in Hindi cinema during late 80s to early 2000s. One of the most prominent singers of 1990s era Bollywood, she has received several accolades, including two National Film Awards, two Bengal Film Journalists'' Association Awards and seven Filmfare Awards for Best Female Playback Singer from thirty-seven nominations. Alka has been described in the media as one of the greatest and most influential singers in Hindi cinema. She is cited as the ''Melody Queen'' of Indian Cinema. Alka is one of the most successful and most popular female singers who reigned the Bollywood music industry for over two decades.
